==English==

===Adverb===
'''[[between]] [[a]] [[rock]] [[and]] [[a]] [[hard]] [[place]]'''

# {{idiom}} Having the choice between two [[unpleasant]] or [[distasteful]] options; in a [[predicament]] or [[quandary]].
#:''I'm '''between a rock and a hard place''' on this negotiation; I need a car, but not at these prices.''

